8. useLayoutEffect
Definition

Works like useEffect but runs before DOM painting.

Example
useLayoutEffect(()=>{
 console.log("Runs before paint")
},[])
9. useImperativeHandle

Used with forwardRef to control exposed methods.

Example:

useImperativeHandle(ref,()=>({
 focus: ()=>inputRef.current.focus()
}))
Custom Hooks

Custom hooks allow reusable logic.

Example

function useCounter(){

 const [count,setCount] = useState(0)

 const increment = ()=>setCount(count+1)

 return {count,increment}
}

Usage

const {count,increment} = useCounter()
